		<poi type="ul.ulsl.sm.cag4.Crafting" mapid="50" xpos="-235.2133" ypos="19.63136" zpos="337.1669" GUID="kQDI/5XZvUarnIjbUF0b4g==" info="[- CRAFTING (30-150) -]&#xA;Depending on where your crafting levels are refine materials/combine luck until it turns gray (receiving zero xp from craft).&#xA;&#xA;[- CRAFTING LEVEL 30-150 -]&#xA;this is the last stretch of crafting we need to do. The gw2crafts.net link for artificing has been copied. Paste it into your browser and do what you need to in order to hit 150 crafting.&#xA;&#xA;with this site you can put in a gw2 api key and get exact details on what to craft, or, you can do your own thing. Hit crafting level 150 and then continue.&#xA;&#xA;[- NOTE -]&#xA;if you level/have leveled handiworker crafting it is account wide and you dont need to worry about leveling crafting.&#xA;&#xA;[- IMPORTANT NOTE -]&#xA;be sure to craft 4 actual items of the same rarity while you are here. You will need them for the mystic forge in the step that follows." inforange="10" copy="https://gw2crafts.net/f2p/artificing.html" copy-message="GW2Crafts Artificing Link copied" minimapvisibility="0" mapvisibility="0" iconsize="1.8" autotrigger="1" triggerrange="8" heightOffset="2" iconfile="data/sl/sl_vol-four_crafting.png" />
		<poi type="ul.ulsl.sm.dmgtype.power" mapid="50" xpos="-166.4525" ypos="22.20867" zpos="190.9083" guid="Eyy+fWf550yjzLvTwaRi9A==" info="[- PURCHASE UPGRADES / RESTOCK -]&#xA;Depending on what boosters/buffs you have you may be just a bit over leveled or WAY over leveled but either way you probably feel a bit squishy. So take this time to fix that.&#xA;&#xA;*** DO NOT SKIP DOING UPGRADES! ***&#xA;&#xA;[- FOOD / UTILITY -]&#xA;• Bowl of Candy Corn Custard&#xA;• Quality Sharpening Stone&#xA;&#xA;[- ARMOR / WEAPON UPGRADES -]&#xA;This process will always be the same&#xA;• Click the cog icon&#xA;• Make the level range -5/+1 current level&#xA;• Click the first dropdown and select power&#xA;• Click the fifth dropdown and select fine/masterwork&#xA;• Sort by price and buy&#xA;   +What is cheapest&#xA;   +What is closest in level&#xA;• Click through each category and repeat&#xA;&#xA;[- OPTIONAL ITEMS -]&#xA;• (4) Rune of Vampirism&#xA;• (2) Rune of the Warrior&#xA;• (2) Sigil of Blood&#xA;• (2) Sigil of Fire&#xA;" inforange="10" minimapvisibility="0" mapvisibility="0" iconsize="1.8" heightOffset="3.5" iconfile="data/sl/sl_tp.png" />
		<poi type="ul.ulsl.sm.dmgtype.condi" mapid="50" xpos="-166.4525" ypos="22.20867" zpos="190.9083" guid="Yj+PTfNDNUawwCePldgG2Q==" info="[- PURCHASE UPGRADES / RESTOCK -]&#xA;Depending on what boosters/buffs you have you may be just a bit overleveled or way overleveled but either way you probably feel a bit squishy. So take this time to fix that.&#xA;&#xA;*** DO NOT SKIP DOING UPGRADES! ***&#xA;&#xA;[- FOOD / UTILITY -]&#xA;• Bowl of Candy Corn Custard&#xA;• Artisan Tuning Crystal&#xA;&#xA;[- ARMOR / WEAPON UPGRADES -]&#xA;This process will always be the same&#xA;• Click the cog icon&#xA;• Make the level range -5/+1 current level&#xA;• Click the first dropdown and select condition&#xA;• Click the fifth dropdown and select fine/masterwork&#xA;• Sort by price and buy&#xA;   +What is cheapest&#xA;   +What is closest in level&#xA;• Click through each category and repeat&#xA;&#xA;[- OPTIONAL ITEMS -]&#xA;• (4) Rune of Scavenging&#xA;• (2) Rune of the Necromancer&#xA;• (2) Sigil of Blood&#xA;• (2) Sigil of Fire" inforange="10" minimapvisibility="0" mapvisibility="0" iconsize="1.8" heightOffset="3.5" iconfile="data/sl/sl_tp.png" />
